## Prioritized remediation sequence

**Immediate priorities, 0–90 days:** Build DFS 504 CDE inventory; document high-risk end-to-end lineage flows; establish daily/periodic reconciliation evidence; inventory manual workarounds; create centralized issue log; add DFS 504 lineage to DGC agenda; define certification evidence package.

**Near-term priorities, 3–6 months:** Expand field-level lineage; implement data quality scorecards; formalize lineage impact assessments in change management; strengthen vendor lineage controls; build alert-to-reporting lineage; define decision rights and approval thresholds.

**Medium-term priorities, 6–12 months:** Automate reconciliations; implement lineage tooling or data catalog integration; mature independent validation; automate data quality monitoring; rationalize manual processes; maintain a complete DFS 504 control matrix tied to annual certification.








